PMID: 35766087 [Indexed for MEDLINE]


898. Rev Bras Epidemiol. 2022 Jun 24;25(Supl 1):e220009. doi: 
10.1590/1980-549720220009.supl.1. eCollection 2022.

Potential years of life lost to cancer in Mato Grosso, stratified by sex: 2000 
to 2019.

[Article in English, Portuguese]

Galvão SM(1)(2), Atanaka M(3), Sousa NFDS(3), Galvão ND(3).

Author information:
(1)Universidade Federal de Mato Grosso, Law School - Cuiabá (MT), Brazil.
(2)Universidade Federal de Mato Grosso, Institute for Collective Health, 
Postgraduate Program - Cuiabá (MT), Brazil.
(3)Universidade Federal de Mato Grosso, Institute for Collective Health - Cuiabá 
(MT), Brazil.

OBJECTIVE: To estimate the potential years of life lost (PYLL) to cancer in the 
State of Mato Grosso, from 2000 to 2019, stratified by sex, according to age 
groups and cancer types.
METHODS: It is a quantitative study with an ecological approach developed from 
secondary data, using the PYLL and its derivatives.
RESULTS: In the period analyzed, deaths from cancer in Mato Grosso resulted in 
680,338 PYLL before the age of 80, with a variation of 82.5%. Of this total, 
52.7% were assigned to males. The rate of the PYLL for cancer before the age of 
60 was 70.9% in males, and 80.1% among women. The rates of PYLL increased in the 
period and showed slightly higher values in males. In the analysis according to 
age group, the rates of PYLL were also higher in males, except between the ages 
of 30 and 49. Lung cancers and lymphomas/leukemias resulted in greater losses of 
PYLL among men and female specific cancers (breast, cervical and uterine, and 
ovarian cancer) accounted for 36.26% of the PYLL among women, with variability 
per age groups.
CONCLUSION: In Mato Grosso, the PYLL indicator for cancer presented unfavorable 
evolution between 2000 and 2019, with greater damage for males and for the 
younger population. Leukemias, lymphomas, and lung and breast cancers were the 
main causes for the PYLL.

